<section class="section">
  <div class="container content">
    <p>Ten of Cups Ceramics is a small studio practice rooted in the making of everyday objects. The studio is named for the tarot card of the same name — a card associated with contentment, gratitude, and the simple pleasures of a life well-lived.</p>
    <p>All work is wheel-thrown and hand-finished. Glazes are mixed in-house. Each piece is fired in a small electric kiln and is intended to be used daily — to hold your coffee, your soup, your flowers.</p>
    <p>Pieces are made in small batches, which means stock is limited. If something sells out and you'd like to be notified when it returns, reach out via the contact page.</p>
  </div>
</section>

